    "import math"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "65d19e71",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Suppose we collect data for a group of students in a statistics class\n",
    "with variables $X_1=$ hours studied, $X_2=$ undergrad GPA, and $Y =$\n",
    "receive an A. We fit a logistic regression and produce estimated\n",
    "coefficient, $\\hat{\\beta}_0 = -6$, $\\hat{\\beta}_1 = 0.05$, $\\hat{\\beta}_2 = 1$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a31b0c4e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "(a) Estimate the probability that a student who studies for 40 h and\n",
    "has an undergrad GPA of 3.5 gets an A in the class."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "421eb6c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "0.3775406687981454\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "y = -6 + 0.05 * 40 + 1 * 3.5\n",
    "prob = 1 / (1 + math.exp(-y))\n",
    "print(prob)  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "18337884",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "(b) How many hours would the student in part (a) need to study to\n",
    "have a 50 % chance of getting an A in the class?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "39f5e5f5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "0.5 = 1 / (1 + e^(-y))\n",
    "\n",
    "-> 0.5 + 0.5 * e^(-y) = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "-> e^(-y) = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "-> -y = 0 = y\n",
    "\n",
    "y = -6 + 0.05 * hr + 1 * 3.5 = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "-> hr = (6 - 1 * 3.5) / 0.05"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "fb1eca6f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "50.0\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "hr = (6 - 1 * 3.5) / 0.05\n",
    "print(hr)"
   ]
  }
